{"TopicId":207655,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Science News Thread (for articles that don\u0026#039;t relate to ongoing discussions)","CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-09T14:54:26Z","PageNum":40,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-09T17:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702142024\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224249\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AckSed\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, AckSed said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll exert the effort\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly wish I could give another up-thumb!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-09T22:10:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702142024\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224249\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AckSed\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AckSed said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve already spent two hours on this so I will admit that for \u003Cem\u003Eairlines\u003C/em\u003E, it\u0027s weak.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about replacing much of the aluminum bulkheads and stringers in aircraft?\u00A0 The skin?\u00A0 Costs could also come down quite a bit if aircraft and auto manufacturer boom the market scale for it, in the longer run, and scarcity is not a big issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m also curious about the fatigue curve vs aircraft Al alloys\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T09:53:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do explosives \u0022flow\u0022 around obstacles?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m specifically wondering what would happen if an ERA brick went off next to a rifle stuck out of a vehicle firing port. Let\u0027s omit the fact that ERA-equipped vehicles tens to have the firing ports plated over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.74\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022899\u0022 src=\u0022https://karopka.ru/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c13/900_600_1/photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222108304_original.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022375\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/starcom68/13305126/2108304/2108304_original.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://gunsfriend.ru/wp-content/uploads/8/a/e/8ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T14:08:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be something weaker than HEAT coming in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd even weaker than an uranium arrow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T14:12:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702288402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do explosives \u0022flow\u0022 around obstacles?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m specifically wondering what would happen if an ERA brick went off next to a rifle stuck out of a vehicle firing port. Let\u0027s omit the fact that ERA-equipped vehicles tens to have the firing ports plated over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://karopka.ru/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c13/900_600_1/photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.74\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022899\u0022 src=\u0022https://karopka.ru/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c13/900_600_1/photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/starcom68/13305126/2108304/2108304_original.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222108304_original.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022375\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/starcom68/13305126/2108304/2108304_original.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://gunsfriend.ru/wp-content/uploads/8/a/e/8ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00228ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://gunsfriend.ru/wp-content/uploads/8/a/e/8ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would guess it would be loosely analogous t\u003Cspan\u003Eo cross-section size of ports minus cross-section size of obstruction at port (like piston diameter in hydraulics) and distance (determining amount of force applied)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-11T14:12:57Z\u0022 title=\u002212/11/2023 02:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 11\u0022\u003EDecember 11, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by darthgently\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T14:30:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702303681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be something weaker than HEAT coming in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd even weaker than an uranium arrow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m more interested in whether ERA and firing ports are compatible at all. Omitting exotic variants such as fixed firing port weapons like the M231.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T15:49:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702305014\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m more interested in whether ERA and firing ports are compatible at all. Omitting exotic variants such as fixed firing port weapons like the M231.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy understanding is that ERA uses a highly directional shaped charge aimed outward.\u00A0 The pressure wave to an adjacent port is probably much less than along the main vector\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Codraroll","CreatedById":163815,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T18:13:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702309775\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy understanding is that ERA uses a highly directional shaped charge aimed outward.\u00A0 The pressure wave to an adjacent port is probably much less than along the main vector\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNecessarily, there will also be a pressure wave going back towards the vehicle. Symmetry of forces and all that. I guess it would propagate through the vehicle and give all the rifles in the firing ports a great big smack that might permanently screw up their aim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems that some people were asleep during that part of physics class:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.78\u0022 height=\u0022650\u0022 width=\u0022959\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-11T18:15:09Z\u0022 title=\u002212/11/2023 06:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 11\u0022\u003EDecember 11, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Codraroll\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-11T19:04:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702318436\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163815\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Codraroll\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, Codraroll said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNecessarily, there will also be a pressure wave going back towards the vehicle. Symmetry of forces and all that. I guess it would propagate through the vehicle and give all the rifles in the firing ports a great big smack that might permanently screw up their aim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems that some people were asleep during that part of physics class:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.78\u0022 height=\u0022650\u0022 width=\u0022959\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill, I\u0027d rather have windshield stuff coming in at velocity N then an RPG exploding inside the cab with larger pieces at N x 1000 velocity.\u00A0 But point seriously taken.\u00A0 None are good options\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T06:16:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702305014\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m more interested in whether ERA and firing ports are compatible at all. Omitting exotic variants such as fixed firing port weapons like the M231.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-1 man vs -7 men\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, there are non-explosive systems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702318436\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163815\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Codraroll\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Codraroll said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems that some people were asleep during that part of physics class:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, because they don\u0027t know that pressure = force/area, and that the total mass of the carriage is too great for one small charge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it\u0027s anyway hard to take aim from the moving APC, so the accuracy isn\u0027t affected too much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T08:17:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShaped charges are highly directional.\u00A0 One can stand behind a claymore and not get pulverized.\u00A0 There is a reason it reads \u0022FRONT TOWARD ENEMY\u0022 on the dangerous side.\u00A0 I\u0027m not saying it would be comfortable inside the cabin with gun ports when the armor went off, but much better than not partially redirecting an incoming RPG\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Codraroll","CreatedById":163815,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T20:02:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702361762\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, there are non-explosive systems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAye, plenty of examples there too:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FPrSSyJXEAEj7l-?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=large\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002280.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FPrSSyJXEAEj7l-?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=large\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T20:49:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702288402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/11/2023 at 10:53 AM, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do explosives \u0022flow\u0022 around obstacles?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m specifically wondering what would happen if an ERA brick went off next to a rifle stuck out of a vehicle firing port. Let\u0027s omit the fact that ERA-equipped vehicles tens to have the firing ports plated over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://karopka.ru/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c13/900_600_1/photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.74\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022899\u0022 src=\u0022https://karopka.ru/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c13/900_600_1/photo_1_1585734605.JPG\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/starcom68/13305126/2108304/2108304_original.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222108304_original.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022375\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/starcom68/13305126/2108304/2108304_original.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://gunsfriend.ru/wp-content/uploads/8/a/e/8ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00228ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://gunsfriend.ru/wp-content/uploads/8/a/e/8ae7f15d0f6d168d598a9efd3d466971.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThink gun ports on APC has fallen out of use quite a bit. They are pretty pointless then driving around as you get bumped around and has very limited visibility. Then stopped the infantry should most time go out and fight as infantry.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf environment is to dangerous as in lots of shell fire, don\u0027t stop. Russia learned they also made the infantry wanting to fight from inside the APC rater than outside.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThink remote gun stations is an much better idea as they are stabilized and can have good optic.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd explosive reactive armor is dangerous for the tank and more so for people around it, you accept loosing some systems. (An use for an dual gun tank? Second gun projectile is 10 meter behind and almost hypersonic\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E \u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702318436\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163815\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Codraroll\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/11/2023 at 7:13 PM, Codraroll said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNecessarily, there will also be a pressure wave going back towards the vehicle. Symmetry of forces and all that. I guess it would propagate through the vehicle and give all the rifles in the firing ports a great big smack that might permanently screw up their aim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems that some people were asleep during that part of physics class:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.78\u0022 height=\u0022650\u0022 width=\u0022959\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GBARQ4nXMAAr3eb?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=medium\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes this looks just stupid, use cage armor instead. One idea to protect armored cars is something like external airbag who grabs the RPG, it probably not even detonate like mostly on cage armor and if it does the stand of distance is increased. Yes it would need lots of sensors to activate more so an an rpg is not powered in flight. If you are in an armored car and targeted by an guided anti tank missile, you have very serious problems.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Codraroll","CreatedById":163815,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T22:33:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702414164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are in an armored car and targeted by an guided anti tank missile, you have very serious problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinding oneself in a Scooby Doo van in the middle of hostile RPG territory is the culmination of pretty poor life choices all around. Weighing the poor engine down with explosive blocks that limit the vision of the driver will not be the ticket out of there, to put it like that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Or probably, it will. Just not in the direction of home. Well, not \u003Cem\u003Ejust\u003C/em\u003E in the direction of home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-12T22:46:18Z\u0022 title=\u002212/12/2023 10:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 12\u0022\u003EDecember 12, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Codraroll\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T23:14:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702414164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThink remote gun stations is an much better idea as they are stabilized and can have good optic.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the take home.\u00A0 With robotic parts and electronic optics off the shelf now definitely the way to go\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-13T06:17:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, T-55 is the best APC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IDF_Achzarit\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IDF_Achzarit\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should restart its production.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SunlitZelkova","CreatedById":206402,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-14T00:13:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346895\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702448275\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, T-55 is the best APC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IDF_Achzarit\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IDF_Achzarit\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should restart its production.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ru.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/QN-506\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://ru.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/QN-506\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nType 59 (T-54) chassis, basically BMP Terminator Chinese style.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AckSed","CreatedById":224249,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T00:41:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHoneybee Robotics developing a solar \u003Cs\u003Estick insect\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Emesh network\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Esurveillance tower\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Estreet light\u003C/s\u003E ALL of them: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T00:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224347342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702600914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224249\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AckSed\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, AckSed said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHoneybee Robotics developing a solar \u003Cs\u003Estick insect\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Emesh network\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Esurveillance tower\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Estreet light\u003C/s\u003E ALL of them: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a great niche to tackle.\u00A0 Clever\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T04:46:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224347342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702600914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224249\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AckSed\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AckSed said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHoneybee Robotics developing a solar \u003Cs\u003Estick insect\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Emesh network\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Esurveillance tower\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003Estreet light\u003C/s\u003E ALL of them: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.honeybeerobotics.com/news-events/honeybee-robotics-to-develop-lunarsaber-for-darpas-luna-10-program/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HBR-LUNARSABER-Street-Light-Perspective-\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.honeybeerobotics.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/HBR-LUNARSABER-Street-Light-Perspective-1024x576.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA mystically glowing lunar fog under the mast.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre they aware, that there is no air on the Moon, so the light spot will be almost invisible from distance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AckSed","CreatedById":224249,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T13:43:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224347368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702615578\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA mystically glowing lunar fog under the mast.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre they aware, that there is no air on the Moon, so the light spot will be almost invisible from distance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt says to me, \u0022We took the first person we could find in the office with Blender skills and told them to finish this render over the weekend.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe thing that makes me blink a bit is that this is supposed to be \u003Cem\u003E100 metres\u003C/em\u003E tall. It can work, especially in Lunar gravity with no air, but if they pack all those collapsible booms, thin-film solar panels, electronics and lights on the top into the base, this is going to have the structural integrity of a crisp packet. It won\u0027t need more, but \u003Cem\u003Estill\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-15T13:49:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2023 01:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 15\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by AckSed\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T15:04:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should add a rotating disco ball on top, rotating in the heat flow from surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-15T19:46:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://blogs.nasa.gov/sunspot/2023/12/12/engineers-working-to-resolve-issue-with-voyager-1-computer/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://blogs.nasa.gov/sunspot/2023/12/12/engineers-working-to-resolve-issue-with-voyager-1-computer/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVoyager starts sending binary data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/gsNaR6FRuO0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022The Sound of dial-up Internet\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/1Y9V0yfO1T0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Zx Spectrum loading sounds - 10 HOURS\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-16T12:25:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTL:DR The Earth was already experiencing volcanic winters (up to -10\u00B0C global anomaly) and choking on toxic fumes before the asteroid offed the dinosaurs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ERecurring volcanic winters during the latest Cretaceous: Sulfur and fluorine budgets of Deccan Traps lavas\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo events share the stage as main drivers of the Cretaceous-Paleogene mass extinction-Deccan Traps volcanism, and an asteroid impact recorded by the Chicxulub crater. We contribute to refining knowledge of the volcanic stressor by providing sulfur and fluorine budgets of Deccan lavas from the Western Ghats (India), which straddle the Cretaceous-Paleogene boundary. Volcanic fluorine budgets were variable (400 to 3000 parts per million) and probably sufficient to affect the environment, albeit only regionally. The highest sulfur budgets (up to 1800 parts per million) are recorded in Deccan lavas emplaced just prior (within 0.1 million years) to the extinction interval, whereas later basalts are generally sulfur-poor (up to 750 parts per million). Independent evidence suggests the Deccan flood basalts erupted in high-flux pulses. Our data suggest that volcanic sulfur degassing from such activity could have caused repeated short-lived global drops in temperature, stressing the ecosystems long before the bolide impact delivered its final blow at the end of the Cretaceous.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37792933/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37792933/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AckSed","CreatedById":224249,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-08T13:06:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA gifts a Phase 1 grant to a new way of cooling I haven\u0027t ever considered - bling!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/general/electro-luminescently-cooled-zero-boil-off-propellant-depots/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/general/electro-luminescently-cooled-zero-boil-off-propellant-depots/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy using all the normal approaches (vacuum insulation, thermal shields), and then plating the non-sunward side of a fuel depot in LEDs, you just might be able to achieve zero boil-off storage of H2, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.esa.int/gsp/ACT/projects/electroluminescent_cooling_using_LEDs/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethanks to a little quirk of physics\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}